{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 ICT AUTHORITY \u8211- Service Delivery\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Cover Page\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Ministry/Department/Agency (MDA):} Ministry of Information, Communications and the Digital Economy\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Department:} ICT Authority (ICTA)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Process Name:} Government ICT Project Implementation and Digital Infrastructure Management\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Document Version:} 2.1\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Date:} 2026-03-04\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Classification:} Official\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Executive Summary\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The ICT Authority (ICTA) is the principal implementing agency responsible for coordinating, implementing, and standardizing ICT initiatives across the Government of Kenya.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Operating under the State Department for ICT and the Digital Economy, ICTA ensures that government ICT investments align with the Government Enterprise Architecture (GEA), national digital standards, and cybersecurity frameworks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ICTA provides centralized capabilities including: - ICT project oversight and technical approvals - Government digital infrastructure implementation - Interoperability and shared platforms - Government cloud and data center management - Digital standards and architecture enforcement\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Currently, ICT projects are often implemented at the MDA level with varying degrees of coordination, resulting in fragmented systems and duplication of infrastructure.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The future state introduces a platform-based government architecture where ICTA operates shared national digital infrastructure including: - Government Cloud - KeSEL / X-Road Interoperability Layer - National PKI - Digital identity integrations - Shared digital services platforms\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This transition enables whole-of-government interoperability, improved security, and efficient digital service delivery.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
