{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Pain Points & Opportunities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Pain Points\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Fragmented Digital Systems:} Multiple government systems operate independently without integration.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Duplicated Infrastructure:} Different agencies procure similar ICT infrastructure.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Limited Interoperability:} Data exchange between MDAs is often manual or through batch exports.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Procurement Complexity:} Long procurement cycles slow the deployment of digital services.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Opportunities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Shared Government Platforms:} Centralized infrastructure including government cloud and national interoperability platforms.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Secure Interoperability:} Adoption of KeSEL / X-Road for secure data exchange.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Digital Trust Infrastructure:} Integration with National PKI and digital identity frameworks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Platform-Based Service Delivery:} Reusable government services such as payments, notifications, identity verification, and registries.\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 2. TO-BE Process Flowchart (BPMN 2.0)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\i Future State visualization (Shared Digital Infrastructure & Platform Government).}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 {\pict\pngblip\picw346\pich1462\picwgoal6920\pichgoal29240 }\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li0 \fi0 TO_BE Diagram\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Future State Process (TO-BE)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Narrative\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b TO-BE Process: Platform-Based Government ICT Implementation}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 ICT Authority transitions from merely reviewing ICT projects to operating shared digital government platforms.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Design Principles:} - {\b Architecture First:} All ICT initiatives must align with Government Enterprise Architecture (GEA) before implementation. - {\b Shared Platforms:} Instead of each agency building separate systems, MDAs use shared government platforms and APIs. - {\b Interoperability by Default:} Systems exchange data through KeSEL (X-Road) ensuring standardized integration. - {\b Cloud-First Government:} All government digital services are deployed on Government Cloud Infrastructure. - {\b Secure Digital Trust:} Systems utilize National PKI, identity verification services, and cybersecurity frameworks.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Optimized Steps (Digital)\par}
